description.plain:
“Glue Song” is a love song about finding someone special and becoming attached to them. beabadoobee sings about experiencing this unexpected connection with someone that is unlike anything she has ever felt before, using glue as a metaphor to symbolize the bond she feels to her new partner.

On October 28, 2022, prior to its release, bea performed this song live for the first time during her concert at the Brooklyn Steel in Brooklyn, New York while on her Beatopia Tour. She then posted an Instagram Reel of her live performance the following day on October 29th, 2022.

The song’s cover art seems to be inspired by the album cover of Kokyuu by Lily Chou-Chou, as when placed next to each other, there are clear similarities between the two.



Side -by-side of the two covers.

annotations: [Outro]

The outro describes a sense of awe or admiration for someone else. The repetition of “I’ve never known” suggests that beabadoobee is reflecting on how this person is unique or different from anyone they’ve encountered before.

The phrase “someone like you” emphasizes that this admiration is specifically directed at the person in question, rather than a more general feeling about the world or other people. The repetition of the line “I’ve never known” reinforces the idea that this is a significant realization for beabadoobee and one that they are still processing.

Overall, the outro uses repetition and a sense of wonder to convey a feeling of respect or fascination for someone else, whose qualities are seen as remarkable or special.
[Chorus]

The lyrics describe feeling stuck or attached to someone else as if held in place by glue. The repetition of “I’ve been stuck by glue” emphasizes this feeling and suggests that it’s a persistent sensation that the speaker can’t shake.

The line “I’m not wrong when I say I’ve been stuck” suggests that beabadoobee is aware of this attachment, and perhaps even feels a sense of resignation about it. The phrase “onto you” reinforces the idea that this attachment is specific to another person, rather than a more abstract feeling of being stuck in general.

Overall, the chorus uses vivid imagery to convey a sense of emotional entanglement and attachment to another person, which the speaker finds difficult to break free from.

I’ve never known someone like you
 Tangled in love, stuck by you

The introduction of the song expresses her astonishment because of the person she’s with. Her mentioning how she hasn’t met someone like her lover, is implying that her lover seems perfect to her. There’s a play of words as Love stuck sounds similar to Love-struck.

Beabadoobee changes Love-struck to Love stuck which shows how the similarity of the word expresses the intense romantic feeling she has for her lover as well as how it causes her to be attach to them. She loses herself to love as she is ‘tangled’ up in love.

Finding the right words
 To use for this song
 I have you in mind
 So it won’t take so long
 Never thought I’d find you
 But you’re here
 And so I love you

These lines are very similar to verse 2 in Lovesong which goes,

“I’m running over sentences at times
I’d better quit dreaming just so I could write
Yet the words to describe you
Aren’t so hard to find
Like a good quote from a book that I’ve memorised”

This indicates that Beabadoobee had found it difficult to write the song down but when her lover is in mind, it makes it easier for her to come up with ideas. This could also indicate how her lyrical skill is dependent on something that brings joy in her life as well as comfort. The fact that she knows she has someone by her side, it makes it easier to overcome her challenging tasks. She also mentions how she hadn’t expected to find a lover like the one she has at the moment which shows her appreciation and how their presence means a lot to her

description.plain:
“death bed (coffee for your head),” released alongside Some Boring, Love Stories, Pt. 2, is a collaboration between Powfu and beabadoobee. The song samples “Coffee” from London artist beabadoobee. In the song, Powfu reminisces on memories with a supposed former lover.

The song delivers two themes of one being the narrator writing this as a tribute to a breakup, or the narrator writing this to address his lover because of upcoming death.

“death bed (coffee for your head)” was first released on February 9, 2019, to all streaming services, but eventually taken down due to Powfu using an unauthorized sample. It was re-released a year later on February 7, 2020, to all streaming platforms. It gained popularity after being featured in many videos on the video platform TikTok.

annotations: Soon you’ll be alone, sorry that you have to lose me

It’s a deep song. And so I try not to make it dark. I tried to incorporate happy things into it, like talking about heaven and that there’s more than just life. And basically I’m just saying, I’m sorry that I’m leaving you because we’re best friends and we rely on each other. So I feel bad leaving her on earth by herself.
Sundays, went to church, on Mondays, watched a movie

So I grew up going to church, so every Sunday I’ll go with my family and I actually met my girlfriend at church, so that’s how we connected. And then Mondays or weekdays we usually just chill, watch movies together and do all that stuff. My favorite movie is ‘Dear John’ by Nicholas Sparks, he wrote the book for it. It has Channing Tatum in it and Amanda Seyfried, who I think are sick actors and it hits my heart every time I watch it. He has problems with his dad and problems with his girlfriend and it’s just, I feel like it’s a sick story. It’s a great story. Really well written.
And sneak out through your kitchen at exactly 1:03
I feel like a common curfew for people is midnight. So I was like, I have to make it past midnight, otherwise, it’s not anything. And then three rhymes so I was like, let’s do 1:03.

Taking goofy videos and walking through the park
 You would jump into my arms every time you heard a bark

Me and my girlfriend will always take her dogs for walks. And so we’ll go down to this big park that’s by her house or whatever and we’ll walk through there every time we hang out usually. Basically I always like filming random stuff and trying to be funny, but I never ended up posting it cause it’s not funny. But me and my girlfriend, we’ll just film random stuff, make TikToks and stuff. And I always think it’s hilarious.
When me and you were younger, you would always make me cheer up

Basically all the cute little date things that we did would make me cheer up. So like going for walks in parks or going to crummy little coffee shops and all the basic things I guess. Thinking about flashbacks and memories and how much fun we had as kids growing up together.
I’m happy that you here with me, I’m sorry if I tear up

I actually don’t tear up too much. It’s yeah, I like before I had my girlfriend, I didn’t cry for like three years straight probably.  I feel like when I’m with my girl though, I get more emotional, she brings out all the deep things.

Don’t stay awake for too long, don’t go to bed
 I’ll make a cup of coffee for your head
 It’ll get you up and going out of bed

For the hook, it kind of just sounds like her boyfriend whatever sleeping and she’s getting him a cup of coffee, which I feel like is the way most people would look at it. And that’s how I looked at it first too. But then I kind of wanted to add my own twist to it and kind of make it a deeper meaning. And so I looked at it from the standpoint of the person that’s dying.

My life was kinda short, but I got so many blessings
 Happy you were mine, it sucks that it’s all ending

I’ve been really blessed. Basically I grew up in a home with three younger siblings who all care for me a lot. So, and I have two loving parents, so basically that’s like super blessed to a lot compared to a lot of people. So that’s what I was talking about in that part.

’Cause yeah, we still young, there’s so much we haven’t done
 Getting married, start a family, watch your husband with his son

I’m 20 years old. So then, I just kind of merged it into my own kind of life and what I would be feeling if that situation was happening in my life at this point. And a lot of my viewers are also around the same age as me, so I feel like they connect more with it. If I were to talk about it at the age I am now. I’m like talking to her while she’s beside my deathbed and I’m just reminding her of all the cool things we did and that I’m thankful for it.

I been praying for forgiveness, you’ve been praying for my health
 When I leave this earth, hopin’ you’ll find someone else

I was in the end of the notebook, there’s a scene where the older guy is dying, and so I was kind of thinking of that at the time. I was thinking of old age but in the song, it kind of sounds like I’m talking about like cancer or something like a more common sickness I guess. I was inspired by the old age part.

annotations: If I told you, you’d know how to go and break my heart in two

The Perfect Pair is a song about believing in perfect relationships, primarily  focusing on the naivety that comes from believing every relationship, especially one’s first ones will be perfect.

Lines like this reference specifically one of her first serious relationships- this one with Arion Krstic, whom she believed was manipulative just because their relationship didn’t turn out perfect. In this line, she is talking about Arion purposefully breaking her heart as harshly as he could. Bea later in her August 15th, 2022 live, when asked about The Perfect Pair’s lyrics and if Arion was abusive stated,

“Relationships won’t always go as you want, like, sometimes your partner may seem mean but … that doesn’t mean they are a bad person … maybe you just don’t work together well. Like with Arion, yeah going back to what I meant with The Perfect Pair.”

Wish I had known this from the beginning
 We’d find it hard to work out, why we have all this doubt

Beabadoobee has this sense of longing to have known that their relationship wasn’t going to work out due to their similarities. She now reflecting on her decisions to agree to be in the relationship. It seems as though if she had known it wasn’t going to work out, she wouldn’t have gotten with this person. She is also trying to figure out the means to why it isn’t working out

We don’t talk much, guess ’cause nothing has changed
 And I’m not sure I like it, and I’m so tired of fighting
This is probably referring to a fight in a relationship which is clearly lacking communication. They “don’t talk much” due to them waiting for the other one to apologize / try to communicate first.
You ought to know that I think we’re one and the same

Bea sings about how both people in the relationship seem to be complacent with the issues. While both of them have problems with each other, they are both “one in the same” because neither of them do anything about them.

I know you hate it when there’s nothing to say
 I’m not quite sure we’d fix it, guess we’re so used to it

Bea sings about the lack of communication and excitement in this relationship. The pair has run out of things to talk about without fighting. Neither of them are particularly happy with this dynamic, but the avoidant silence is something that they have become used to and she views it as beyond repair at this point.

body.plain: “Tired” is about the stressed and scattered brain of every human out there. It’s about that era, that period, that moment in time we all go through where everything seems pointless and you feel like you’re drowning in an endless pit.

annotations:
To give my brain some extra space to think
 ’Bout all the things to do to help

This verse verse has a double meaning: The speaker’s eating disorder here is used to make more space, so to speak, but it could also reference how the speaker pushes people away for more space.

The speaker in the second space is trying to distract themselves from their issues by helping others, which is in some ways a coping mechanism.
Maybe it’s time to shut away

this could mean to isolate oneself from society possibly because they aren’t happy or energetic which is how society wants them
it could also reinforce the contemplation of suicide

Is it the fact you never say
 What comes in your mind that day?
It could show how the person she is referring to has stopped consolidating in others and possibly is bottling up their emotions
’Cause I’ve been eating less all day

The narrator may also be suffering from an eating disorder, which is common in people with depression. Whether it is due to insecurities or lack of motivation, this is a very unhealthy habit which unfortunately affects many. As her motivation to live runs out, she begins to eat less and less and she slowly starts to slip away.
’Cause I’ve never really felt okay

The narrator has constantly felt this depressing feeling inside. Only now, it is affecting her more than normal where she appears to be at an all time low. This is a chronic and familiar feeling for her.

Maybe it’s time to say goodbye
 ’Cause I’m getting pretty fucking tired

The narrator is in such a dark place in their life where they may be contemplating ending it. They are so tired of everything that they are having trouble sleeping and functioning. This is a chronic feeling. Depression is a very serious mental health issue that many suffer from, which can sadly make this song relatable for many.

You haven’t been good for long
 Is it the sound of your own thoughts
 That always keeps you up at night?

It can be implied that the author is referring to herself when she is saying “you.” She does not like the person she has become and constantly feels empty. Her thoughts distract her at night as she has become so unsatisfied with her life and who she is.

description.plain:
“Coffee” is a light acoustic ballad written by and performed by beabadoobee. In it, Bea lightly touches on the themes of mental health, relationships, and how they play together. In a Vice profile piece, Bea mentions that this song was about her boyfriend, Søren:

It was about my boyfriend, Søren, because he has green eyes. It was about him—it’s the cringiest love song about me making coffee for him.

In an interview with Pigeons with Planes, Bea confirms that this is the first song that she’s written for the guitar.

In the same interview, she also says

I’ve realized I can’t play to a click. ‘Coffee’ is all over the place. The tempo is so wack.

Notably, “Coffee” was sampled on Powfu’s death bed (coffee for your head) in 2019, which was re-released in 2020.

description.plain:
The third track of Beatopia, Sunny Day has an appropriately summery feel, channeling retro vibes as Bea sings about reconnecting with friends after a period of rainy weather.

Beabadoobee once states in a press release:

Sunny Day is a song that I’ve always wanted to make but something that I’ve never done before. Putting it on Beatopia was quite nerve-wracking for me but I’m glad I did. We had written it during a week of crazy productivity in terms of creating songs. I had a session with Starsmith and the song just flowed naturally. I love it.

These lines could be implying some sort of unrequited love. Both Bea and the other person have the capacity to love each other, maybe they are even meant to be together (shown through the line “we both like apple cider”). However, there is a third party that is interrupting their connection, suggested by the person “smelling like fruit punch”, which could imply that they are infatuated with someone else.

Bea could be referring to herself as “apple cider” why the love interest in this song could have their own love interest, who is being referred to as “fruit punch”. This could also explain the line “But your hair be smelling like fruit punch” because the love interest has been around “fruit punch” a lot

she is going out of her way to please the other person because she likes them so much

This song describes Bea trying to convince herself she doesn’t like the other person that much, then she continues with the line ‘wait, i do, fuck’ which shows how she’s suddenly become aware and realises her mistake – she does, in fact, like them very much.

description.plain:
“Talk” is an energetic guitar-driven track where beabadoobee describes her regular days where she’d often go out on a Tuesday night when she should remain at home to relax for her midweek duties for the following morning.

On March 23, 2022, she spoke with NME in an interview, where she’s depicted herself opting to enjoy life:

I wrote ‘Talk’ just after my first album. I was obsessed with Tuesday because I thought it was the best night to go out, not too much chaos but just enough to have a good time. Generally, it’s about doing things that aren’t necessarily healthy or great for you but you can’t help indulging. It’s like that unavoidable feeling that you get, you can’t get rid of it and you know it’s bad but you love it really and it’s whatever, so you do it anyway.

On March 15, 2022, Bea first teased the instrumental on her Twitter, telling her followers to subscribe to her mailing list to stay up to date on her latest releases:

sign up to my mailin list if u wanna be first to find out more…welcome to beatopia <33
